Adaro, Bank Central Asia, Titan Kimia: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-04-21T01:28:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-21/adaro-bank-central-asia-titan-kimia-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  rose 1.7 percent to 3,794.76.  Energy companies: Crude oil futures gained the most in a
month, adding 2.9 percent to $111.45 a barrel in  New York 
yesterday. The contract was at $111.92 a barrel in after-hours
trading as of 7:44 a.m. Jakarta time.  PT Medco Energi Internasional (MEDC IJ), Indonesia’s
biggest listed oil company, fell 0.9 percent to 2,775 rupiah. PT
Benakat Petroleum Energy (BIPI IJ) slid 1.2 percent to 86
rupiah.  Nickel producers: Nickel for three-month delivery jumped
4.4 percent to $26,400 a metric ton in  London  yesterday, the
steepest increase since Jan. 12. PT International Nickel
Indonesia (INCO IJ), the nation’s largest producer of the metal,
gained 2.1 percent to 4,900 rupiah and PT Aneka Tambang (ANTM
IJ), the second biggest, fell 1.1 percent to 2,300 rupiah.  PT Adaro Energy (ADRO IJ):  Indonesia ’s second-biggest coal
producer plans to refinance part of its total debt of $1.6
billion and also expects to complete acquisition talks this year
on two or three mines, Bisnis Indonesia reported, citing David
Tendian and Andre Mamuaya, directors at Adaro. The stock rose
1.1 percent to 2,250 rupiah.  PT Bank Central Asia (BBCA IJ): Indonesia’s largest bank by
market value acquired PT Transpacific General Insurance at a
cost of 40 billion rupiah ($4.6 million), Bisnis Indonesia
reported, citing Jahja Setiaatmadja, vice president director at
Bank Central Asia. The stock gained 1.3 percent to 7,550 rupiah.  PT Titan Kimia Nusantara (FPNI IJ): The company plans to
build a $3 billion to $5 billion ethylene plant in Indonesia’s
Banten province,  Bisnis Indonesia  reported, citing Titan
President Director David Tsu Hung Chao. Titan Kimia advanced 4
percent to 130 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at   dboey@bloomberg.net  